==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle English < Old English '''[[snaca]]''' < Proto-Germanic '''[[*snakon]]''' < Proto-Indo-European base '''[[*snag-]]''', '''[[*sneg-]]''' (to crawl, a creeping thing).

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: snāk
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /sneɪk/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /sneIK/

===Noun===
'''snake''' (pl. [[snakes]])

#A [[legless]] [[reptile]] of the sub-order ''Serpentes''.
#A [[tool]] for unplugging [[plumbing]].

====Synonyms====
*[[serpent]]

